                              ዘወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ተስፋይ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ እግዚአ፡ ኃረያ፡ ወውሉዱ፡ ገብረ፡
                              ሐዋርያ፡ ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ ኪዳነ፡ [<locus target="#67ra">67ra</locus>] ማርያም፡ ገብረ፡
                              ማርያም፡ ተስፋ፡ ማርያም፡ ወእምሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ጻድቃን፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Mention of the commissioner Takla Hāymānot, of his wife Walatta
                              Madḫǝn, his spiritual father Za-Walda Māryām and other members of his
                              family. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Decorated notes in the upper margins indicating
                              the readings for monthly commemorations of the Text I as follows:
                                 <locus target="#11r">Fol. 11r</locus>: zä-Ḫǝdar; <locus target="#16r">Fol. 16r</locus>: zä-Taḥśaś; <locus target="#20v">Fol. 20v</locus>: zä-Ṭǝrr; <locus target="#25r">Fol. 25r</locus>:
                              zä-Yäkätit; <locus target="#28">Fol. 28</locus>: zä-Mäggabit; <locus target="#32r">Fol. 32r</locus>: Miyāzyā; <locus target="#35r">Fol.
                                 35r</locus>: zä-Gǝnbot; <locus target="#40v">Fol. 40v</locus>:
                              zä-Säne; <locus target="#45r">Fol. 45r</locus>: Ḥamle; <locus target="#48v">Fol. 48v</locus>: zä-Näḥise [sic]; <locus target="#53r">Fol. 53r</locus>: zä-Maskaram. -Written in the upper
                              margin, information concerning Text II, in blue pen, as follows:
                                 <locus target="#54r">Fol. 54r</locus>: yä-qal kidan; <locus target="#56r">Fol. 56r</locus>: lä-qoqawmotu (?); <locus target="#66r">Fol. 66r</locus>: zä-ʿǝlätä ʿǝräftu.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
